Now that I have reached Day 27, I finally feel the strength to testify: yoga with Adriene has changed my life. I came to this channel 27 days ago because I had just quit smoking and drinking. In need of something to manage my anxiety disorder, especially during coronavirus lockdown (I have congenital heart disease and am at risk), I was willing to try anything to keep myself clean and healthy. People had recommended yoga to me many times before in my life (I am quite high strung) and though i tried it before, I could never commit to letting go. Now, I am happy to go to the mat each morning and night, I rely on it to get me through the day and help me sleep at night. Thank you Adriene for teaching me the two things that helped me to commit to my healthy life changes: how to breathe and how to let go. Namaste!!!

I decided to give these 30 days of yoga a try, knowing and accepting that it would take me longer than 30 days. During this "challenge" I have had two bouts of strep throat, but struck with it as soon I was recovered. I come from a very athletic family and a mom who is very fit, both things I have never been. I have always had a really hard time finding any type of exercise that stuck with me. Today, I was able to find peace and grace in this new body and overwhelming joy in the simple fact that I was actually able to stay balanced for the entire tree pose as well as actually stick with something for 27 days! Thank you, Adriene for this new sense of peace, acceptance, and even confidence in what my body can do.

I've been so excited for the last 27 days for the day I could finally write this comment: MY FEET WERE FLAT ON THE GROUND DURING DOWNWARD DOG TODAY (!!!) Day by day, they've been getting closer and closer but today was the day they were 100% flat! It felt so amazing; I couldn't stop smiling through the rest of the practice!! <3 

Thank you so much Adriene for this amazing series that has inspired so many people for the last 5 years!

Day 27 âœ”ï¸ I'm becoming less of a negligent and negative friend, and more of a caring counselor and positive friend towards my body. What I mean is that throughout my practice today, a lot of my body wasn't doing what I was telling it to do--my wrist would hurt, shoulder pain would flare up, etc--but instead of talking down and critizing them for not cooperating, I started to modify the practice and continue the flow--I didn't shame them for feeling how they did. I would counsel my wrist and ask "okay, we'll have you tried this?" And then I would go on my fist from open palm and it worked. When shoulder pain would collapse my downward dog, I changed my perspective: that my body was asking for healing because it wanted to go to the floor because it was so tired. I found what felt good and made the practice as much as I could my own while following along. And towards the end, I could feel my body thank me in shavashna; it just needed some support.I was relaxed and yawning so much. This caused me to tear up (not sure if this is due to emotional blockages clearing up or just my tear ducts opening up from all the yawning or both lol), but time slowed down so much, that I could feel the warmth of my tears as they floated out of my eyes and then became cold as they dove down the sides of my face. 

Maybe because my body intelligence found the friend it was looking for all this time, because my mind intelligence is that friend to so many others, but wasn't to myself. Namaste and gratitude to everyone ðŸ™

27 days ago, I had never done yoga. I over ate, drank a little too much vino and hadn't done exercise for about 9 years. My 19 year old daughter introduced me to adriene and I have followed every day since. To begin with, I had zero balance. Tree pose wS impossible for more than 1/2 a second on each side. I couldn't touch the floor in forward fold and even cat and dog poses killed my palms and knees. I had to force myself to commit to the program. Today, I managed tree pose, without holding on to the work top, for a whole minute on my right side and a little less on my left. My palms and knees are no longer a problem and I can rest my palms on the floor in forward fold. I don't WANT to eat or drink anything that isn't beneficial to my health and well being and I'm finding myself wanting to get up 1/2 hour earlier to be able to start my day with yoga, every morning. I feel emotionally and physically completely different...in a great way! Xx
